 Sheopened the medicine chest in her bathroom. "Empty--but I know what I'll putthere." The bedroom "enchanted" her. Ocharovatel'no! (Annette's favoritepraise word.) She criticized, though, the bedside bookshelf: "What, noByron? No Browning? Ah, Coleridge! The little golden sea snakes. Miss Wardgave me an anthology for Russian Easter: I can recite your last duchess--Imean `My Last Duchess' "

I caught my breath with a moan. I kissed her. I wept. I sat, shaking,on a fragile chair that creaked in r